            "description": "</h3>This <i>+2 lance</i> is made out of white spruce wood with a handle carved from mammoth tusk ivory. Its shaft is decorated with images of charging mammoths or running wolves. Traditionally, the owner of a <i>mammoth lance</i> adorns the weapon with small trophies attached via short leather strips or carves notches in the shaft to represent triumphs. When wielded while mounted on a creature with the animal type, a <i>mammoth lance</i> uses the mount\u2019s Strength modifier on damage rolls rather than the wielder\u2019s Strength modifier.<br/><br/> When its wielder is not mounted, or is mounted on a creature without the animal type, a <i>mammoth</i> lance functions as a normal +2 lance.",
