            "cost": "6,000 gp",
            "description": "</h3>This stout, dense rod is always constructed of highly conductive metal, shot through with weblike veins of white or yellow glass. While a creature holds a <i>conduit rod</i>, she gains electricity resistance 5 as a constant effect as well as a +1 bonus to her effective caster level when casting any spell with the electricity descriptor.<br/><br/> Once per day as a free action, when the wielder of a <i>conduit rod </i>casts a spell with the electricity descriptor, she can teleport anywhere that spell\u2019s effect, but is otherwise unaffected by the spell."
