        "requirements": "Forge Ring, greater teleport",
        "cost": "3,000 gp",
        "description": "</h3>The imperial intelligence agency, the Hatharat, entrusts <i>rings of return</i> to agents within Taldor and other hostile regions. When a transport command word is spoken (a standard action), a <i>ring of return</i> whisks the wearer to the nearest imperial administration building within Kelesh’s borders, as if via <i>greater teleport</i>. If anyone attempts to remove a <i>ring of return</i> from the wearer’s finger without speaking a removal command word (a standard action that provokes an attack of opportunity), the attempt triggers the effect, transporting both the wearer and the person attempting to remove the ring. A successful DC 20 Will save allows a character to resist the teleportation, but in any event, a <i>ring of return</i> can be used only once; after its single charge is expended, it becomes an ordinary, nonmagical ring."
