        "description": "</h3>This heavy leather belt is reinforced with metal and detailed to resemble a gut wound that has sprouted teeth. In addition to functioning as a <i>belt of mighty constitution +2</i>, the mouth on the belt animates whenever the wearer gains the grappled condition, damaging the wearer’s opponent as if it were armor spikes (1d6 points of damage for a Medium wearer, 1d4 for Small). Similar to armor spikes, the mouth can be made into a magic weapon in its own right; it can also be temporarily enhanced with magic such as <i>magic weapon</i>. The wearer can use the mouth to eat meat, gaining nutrition from it as if he had eaten with his own mouth (the mouth refuses any food other than meat)."
