        "cl": "5th",
        "slot": "neck",
        "price": "5,400 gp",
        "weight": "—",
        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, lightning bolt , wind wall",
        "cost": "2,700 gp",
        "description": "</h3>A stormlure is usually fashioned from pieces of creatures\r known for their affinity to air—the feathers of birds, the\r shells of flying insects, and the scales of a dragon. When\r activated, stormlures call to the wind, causing a tempestuous\r gale. Once per day on command, the wearer of a stormlure is\r surrounding by swirling winds for 1 minute, granting a 50%\r miss chance against all ranged attacks, including rays and\r other ranged spells that require a roll to hit. This wind does\r not hinder the wearer of the <i>stormlure </i>in any way. At any\r one time during this duration, as a swift action, the wearer\r can cause the air around her to fill with crackling lightning,\r dealing 4d6 points of electricity damage to all creatures\r adjacent to her. A DC 14 Reflex save halves this damage."
