        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, awaken , fox’s cunning",
        "cost": "6,000 gp",
        "description": "</h3>Although it appears to be a simple thong of leather, this collar\r was initially conceived by druids who believed that there were\r animals who possessed spirits worthy of elevation to true\r sentience. If worn by a creature of the animal type with an\r Intelligence less than 3, a <i>collar of the true companion</i> grants\r a +2 enhancement bonus to Intelligence. This does not give the\r animal the ability to speak, but it does allow it to understand\r one spoken language (chosen by the item’s creator).\r<br/><br/>If the collar is worn for at least 1 week by a creature of the\r animal type, the creature is raised to humanlike sentience,\r as though by the <i>awaken </i>spell. Once this occurs, the collar\r loses its magical properties.\r<br/><br/>If a <i>collar of the true companion</i> is worn for more than\r 1 week by a creature not of the animal type, the wearer is\r <i>feebleminded </i>until the collar is removed."
