        "description": "</h3>Drinking this elixir grants the imbiber a +10 bonus on Bluff checks\r made to convince another that her words are the truth. This\r bonus lasts for 10 minutes, and doesn’t apply to any other use of the Bluff skill, such as feinting in combat, creating a diversion to\r hide, or communicating a secret message via innuendo.<br/><br/>\r If a magical effect is used against the <i>honeytongue elixir’s</i>\r imbiber that would detect her lies or force her to speak the\r truth, the user of the effect must succeed at a DC 16 caster\r level check to compel the elixir’s imbiber to tell the truth. Failure\r means the effect doesn’t detect the imbiber’s lies or force her\r to tell the truth."
