      "name": "Beast-bond Brand",
      "details": {
        "aura": "faint abjuration",
        "cl": "5th",
        "slot": "none",
        "price": "1,000 gp",
        "weight": "—",
        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, Reach Spell ( Advanced Player’s Guide ),\r creator must have an animal companion or familiar",
        "cost": "500 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This sticky henna paste is used to stamp a rust-colored handprint\r onto the body of a familiar or animal companion, and a hoof,\r claw, or paw print from that creature onto its master. These\r brands demonstrate a bond of friendship and balance, not\r ownership and subservience. Applying the brand requires a\r full-round action each for master and companion. The brand\r enhances the share spells ability of druids, wizards, and other\r classes with animal companions or familiars, allowing these\r characters to cast spells with a range of personal or touch on the\r marked companion at a range of 30 feet, provided the character\r has line of effect to the creature. Each spell cast at range in this\r way drains one charge from the <i>beast-bond brand</i> for each spell\r level of the spell cast. A newly applied <i>beast-bond brand</i> has 10\r charges. When all charges are consumed, the brand vanishes.\r For the purposes of teleportation spells and effects, the master\r may treat a marked companion as an object or a creature,\r whichever is more favorable (weight restrictions still apply).\r<br/><br/>A character may have only one creature marked in this way\r at any time. The brand lasts until all charges are expended or\r the master marks another companion in this way."
      },
