        "slot": "none",
        "price": "1,150 gp",
        "weight": "3 lbs.",
        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, charm animal , summon nature’s ally I , wild\r empathy ability",
        "cost": "575 gp",
        "description": "</h3>If the possessor learns the proper tune, he can use these\r pipes to attract 1d3 rat swarms if any rats are within 400 feet.\r For each 50-foot distance the rats have to travel, there is a\r 1-round delay. The piper must continue playing until the rats\r appear, and when they do so, the piper must make a DC 10\r Perform (wind instruments) check. Success means that they\r obey the piper’s telepathic commands so long as he continues\r to play. Failure indicates that they turn on the piper. If for any\r reason the piper ceases playing, the rats leave immediately.\r The Perform DC increases by +5 for each time the rats have\r been successfully called in a 24-hour period.\r<br/><br/>If the rats are under the control of another creature, add the\r HD of the controller to the Perform check DC. Once control is\r assumed, another check is required each round to maintain it if\r the other creature is actively seeking to reassert its control."
