        "cost": "750 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This fragile glass flask encloses a single scrap of worn parchment\r held in place by a taut metal wire threaded through its cork\r stopper. As a full-round action, a spellcaster can cast a targeted\r language-dependant spell of 3rd level or lower into the flask as\r a full round action, which covers the parchment with magical\r writing and charges the flask with power. The flask cannot be\r used with spells that have a casting time longer than 1 full round.\r Any of the spell’s variables that are determined by its caster\r (such as commands given to the spell’s target) are decided when\r the spell is cast into the bottle.\r<br/><br/>The charged flask can be thrown as a splash weapon with a\r range increment of 10 feet. The flask shatters and is destroyed\r upon impact, releasing the stored spell. A creature struck by the\r flask is subject to the effects of spell contained within, just as if\r it had been the target of the spell. Creatures within 5 feet of the\r flask when it breaks hear whispery echoes of the spell’s words\r and are also subject to its effects, though they receive a +5 bonus\r on their saves to resist the spell. If the spell does not ordinarily\r allow a save, creatures caught in the splash radius may still make\r a Will save to negate it (with the +5 bonus)."
