        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, control water , disintegrate",
        "cost": "800 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This brown dust is similar to <i>dust of dryness</i>, but affects acid\r rather than water and absorbs less liquid. If it is thrown into\r acid, a volume of as much as 10 gallons is instantly transformed\r into nothingness, and the dust becomes a marble sized pellet\r floating or resting where it was thrown. If this pellet is hurled, it\r breaks and releases the same volume of acid, dealing 1d6 points\r of acid damage per gallon absorbed into the pellet (maximum\r 4d6), affecting all creatures within a 30-foot radius of its point of\r impact. This is a splash weapon.\r<br/><br/>If the dust is used against an ooze that deals acid damage with\r its attacks, the creature must make a DC 18 Fortitude save or be\r destroyed. The dust deals 5d6 points of damage to the ooze even\r if its saving throw succeeds."
