        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, silent image",
        "cost": "1,000 gp",
        "description": "</h3>When hammered into place this 9-inch iron spike creates an\r illusion up to 15 feet high and in a 15-foot diameter centered\r on the spike. The illusion can be of one of the following: a\r small hillock of appropriate composition for the terrain, a pile\r of mundane crates or barrels, a mound of rubble, or a small\r structure (such as a cabin or canvas enclosure). The exact size and\r specific parameters (such the composition of timber) are chosen\r when the spike is placed. Interacting with the illusion grants a\r Will save (DC 12) to disbelieve it.\r<br/><br/>Hammering the spike into place or removing it is a full-round\r action. The spike can be used any number of times and its effects\r last until removed."
