        "slot": "none",
        "price": "2,400 gp",
        "weight": "—",
        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, make whole",
        "cost": "1,200 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This pale amber substance is thick and viscous. Because of its\r particular powers, it can be contained only in a flask whose\r inside has been coated with 1 ounce of <i>salve of slipperiness</i>,\r and each time any of the bonding agent is poured from the\r flask, a new application of the <i>salve of slipperiness</i> must be\r put in the flask within 1 round to prevent the remaining glue\r from adhering to the side of the container. A flask of <i>sovereign\r glue</i>, when found, holds anywhere from 1 to 7 ounces of the\r stuff (1d8–1, minimum 1), with the other ounce of the flask’s\r capacity taken up by the <i>salve of slipperiness</i>. One ounce of\r this adhesive covers 1 square foot of surface, bonding virtually\r any two substances together in a permanent union. The glue\r takes 1 round to set. If the objects are pulled apart (a move\r action) before that time has elapsed, that application of the\r glue loses its stickiness and is worthless. If the glue is allowed\r to set, then attempting to separate the two bonded objects\r has no effect, except when <i>universal solvent</i> is applied to the\r bond. <i>Sovereign glue</i> is dissolved by <i>universal solvent</i>.\r<br/><br/>The price and creation cost given are per ounce."
