        "cost": "2,000 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This 10-foot long rope ladder unrolls itself on command,\r extending upward into the air and magically holding itself\r in place. The ends of each rope have small loops for tying to\r another rope, a grappling hook, a piton, or similar fixtures. A\r second command word makes the ladder roll itself again, pulling\r itself toward whichever end the speaker is touching. Climbing\r the ladder is a DC 0 Climb check. The ladder can hold up to 300\r pounds if holding itself in the air, or 600 pounds if attached to a\r sturdy surface.\r<br/><br/>A third command word creates an extradimensional space\r at the top of the ladder that is identical to <i>rope trick</i>, except\r it only holds up to one Medium creature and has a very short\r duration. When a creature enters the extradimensional space,\r at the end of the creature’s turn the space collapses and the\r creature is transported as though by <i>dimension door</i> 1d6 ×\r 100 feet away in a random direction to a safe, ground-level\r location. The ladder remains behind and falls to the ground\r when this power is used. The third command word may be\r used once per day."
