        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, compel hostility ( Ultimate Combat ), creator\r must have 5 ranks in the Bluff skill",
        "cost": "3,500 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This bright red garment bestows no benefit when worn on\r the shoulders, but when held in one hand while draped\r over the arm, the cape obscures its user’s movements\r in combat. Used this way, the cape bestows a +1 insight\r bonus to AC and a +5 competence bonus on Bluff checks\r to feint in combat. Readying the cape in combat is a move\r action; if the wielder has a base attack bonus of +1 or\r higher, the wielder can ready the cape as a free action as\r part of movement.\r<br/><br/>Once per day as an immediate action, a creature brandishing a\r <i>cape of bravado</i> may attempt to compel an opponent within 30\r feet to attack him on its next turn (Will negates DC 11)."
