        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, alarm , light",
        "cost": "3,500 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This decorative <i>wayfinder </i>appears to be made of gold, and\r its face is marked with white and silver motifs of roosters.\r Whenever the wielder of a <i>noisemaker wayfinder</i> falls asleep,\r the roosters decorating the <i>wayfinder </i>change to crescent moons.\r Whenever a Tiny or larger creature comes within 20 feet of the\r <i>wayfinder’s </i>bearer while she is asleep and this magic item is\r on her person, the <i>noisemaker wayfinder</i> immediately begins\r vibrating, buzzing, and ringing loudly as long as there is a clear\r line of effect between the <i>wayfinder’s </i>bearer and the triggering\r creature. The sound from this effect easily travels 60 feet, as the\r audible <i>alarm </i>version of the <i>alarm </i>spell. A creature that speaks\r the password (determined by the wielder and assigned to the\r <i>wayfinder </i>before she falls asleep) does not set off the alarm.<br/><br/>\r When the <i>wayfinder’s </i>alarm is triggered, the violent motion of\r the <i>noisemaker wayfinder</i> continues until the wielder presses a\r button on the side of the device. If the wielder of a <i>noisemaker\r wayfinder</i> is affected by a magical sleep effect (such as that\r caused by a <i>sleep </i>spell) and the alarm is triggered, the constant\r buzzing and vibration of the <i>wayfinder </i>allows the wielder to\r attempt a saving throw each round at the end of her turn to\r end the sleep effect and gives her a +2 circumstance bonus on\r such saves. Other sleeping creatures within hearing range of the\r <i>wayfinder </i>wake up from normal sleep, but not magical sleep. The\r bearer of a <i>noisemaker wayfinder</i> may disable its audible alarm\r function at will by pressing down on the compass needle."
