        "description": "</h3>Made of a glassy, translucent substance, this orb swirls with the\r eldritch energy of spellcasters long departed. When the bearer\r researches a spell to create a new spell or learn an existing\r one from another source (see Chapter 9 of the <i>Pathfinder RPG\r Core Rulebook</i>), this orb provides a +2 competence bonus on\r Spellcraft checks.<br/><br/>\r Additionally, when the command word is spoken, an <i>orb\r of arcane research</i> allows its bearer to gain a +5 insight\r bonus on a Craft (alchemy), Knowledge (arcana), Knowledge\r (nature), or Spellcraft check made to research a spell or\r extract formula (see page 86 of <i>Ultimate Campaign</i>). The orb\r can be used five times in this way before the item cracks,\r losing all of its magical properties and reverting to a piece of\r mundane glass."
