      "details": {
        "aura": "moderate transmutation",
        "cl": "7th",
        "slot": "none",
        "price": "10,000 gp",
        "weight": "—",
        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, gentle repose , stoneskin",
        "cost": "5,000 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This coarse, acrid-smelling thread is more akin to wire than\r fabric. When carefully sewn into the body of a flesh golem\r or zombie (requiring 1 hour per Hit Die of the creature\r and a successful DC 20 Heal or Spellcraft check), the\r stitches change the creature’s damage reduction to DR 5/\r adamantine and slashing. Variant zombies lacking damage\r reduction (such as fast zombies) instead gain DR 5/slashing.\r One length of stitching is required for every Hit Die of the\r creature being enhanced. Using an insufficient number of\r lengths has no effect. A full thimble of <i>embalming thread</i>\r contains 20 lengths.\r<br/><br/>If the skill check to use the stitches fails, they are not\r wasted, but must first be cleaned and unknotted, requiring\r 1 hour per stitch. Once used successfully, the stitches cannot\r be reused."
      },
