        "cl": "15th",
        "slot": "none",
        "price": "20,000 gp",
        "weight": "10 lbs.",
        "requirements": "Craft Wondrous Item, banishment",
        "cost": "10,000 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This lustrous golden bell produces a deep and resonant ring\r which vibrates in perfect harmony with the Material Plane\r and destructively interferes with otherworldly beings. These\r vibrations reduce the damage reduction and spell resistance\r of all extraplanar creatures within 30 feet by 5 (for example,\r changing DR 10/magic to DR 5/magic). The bell has no clapper;\r to ring it, the bearer must attack it with an unarmed strike (this\r counts as an attack, with no attack roll needed, and does not\r damage the bell). The ringing lasts 1d6 rounds; stifling the\r ringing early is a standard action. It can ring for a maximum of\r 10 rounds per day."
