        "description": "</h3>A<i> racing broom of flying</i> functions like a <i>broom of flying</i>,\r except for 9 minutes per day it can fly faster than its\r standard counterpart. Activating this increased speed is a\r swift action. The broom’s increased fly speed is 60 feet with\r a load up to 200 pounds, or at a speed of 40 feet carrying\r up to 400 pounds. Each minute at this faster speed uses\r 1 hour of the broom’s daily flight time. As a swift action,\r the rider may expend 5 hours of flight time to increase the\r broom’s speed to 120 feet with a load up to 200 pounds, or\r at a speed of 80 feet carrying up to 400 pounds. This speed\r boost lasts for 1 round, but when it ends there is a 50%\r chance that the broom gains the broken condition and is\r powerless until repaired."
