        "cost": "20,000 gp",
        "description": "</h3>This small talisman is comprised of teeth, fingers, ears, or\r other grotesque trophies taken from the freshly dead. Each\r talisman is imbued with an intense animosity toward a\r particular type of creature, chosen from the ranger favored\r enemy list when the fetish is created. Once per day, the\r talisman can impart this animosity to a ranger (or other\r character with the favored enemy class feature), replacing\r one of his favored enemies with the fetish’s designated\r creature type. This lasts 24 hours. To activate the fetish, the\r ranger must spend 10 minutes quietly holding it; he then\r may select one of his favored enemies to replace with the\r item’s favored enemy. For example, a ranger with a +6\r favored enemy bonus against orcs may use a dragon-hating\r fetish, gaining a +6 favored enemy bonus against dragons\r and losing the bonus against orcs for 24 hours. Alternatively,\r once per day, the bearer can activate the fetish as a swift\r action, but its effects only last 10 minutes and the bearer\r only gains half his favored enemy bonus (for example, the\r ranger would lose his orc bonus and only gain a +3 favored\r enemy bonus against dragons for 10 minutes)."
