        "description": "</h3>This featureless gray stone is perfectly smooth and flawlessly\r polished. The bearer of an <i>orb of pure law</i> gains a +4 deflection\r bonus to AC against attacks from chaotic creatures and a +4\r resistance bonus on saving throws against polymorph effects,\r effects with the chaotic descriptor, and effects that inflict the\r confused condition.\r<br/><br/>When held in hand, the bearer of the orb may use <i>detect\r chaos</i> and <i>detect law </i>at will. A lawful creature may hold the\r orb in hand and command it to invoke <i>dispel chaos</i> and <i>arrow\r of law</i> each once per day.\r<br/><br/>The orb bestows one permanent negative level on any\r chaotic creature holding or carrying it. The negative level\r remains as long as the creature has the orb and disappears\r immediately when the orb is no longer held or carried. This\r negative level cannot be overcome in any way (including by\r <i>restoration </i>spells) while the bearer has the orb."
